<paper id="1929884534"><title>A Heuristic for Symmetry Reductions with Scalarsets</title><year>2001</year><authors><author org="Eindhoven University of Technology" id="2072892544">Dragan Bosnacki</author><author org="Eindhoven University of Technology" id="2065067749">Dennis Dams</author><author org="Eindhoven University of Technology" id="2953101474">Leszek Holenderski</author></authors><n_citation>20</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1528929318</reference><reference>1536783297</reference><reference>1544872225</reference><reference>1578523300</reference><reference>1604838600</reference><reference>1728798265</reference><reference>1822079664</reference><reference>1835119762</reference><reference>1868374413</reference><reference>1953283412</reference><reference>1972065960</reference><reference>1984957636</reference><reference>2012935476</reference><reference>2016300863</reference><reference>2055558998</reference><reference>2340735175</reference><reference>2611515161</reference><reference>2912102632</reference></references><venue id="1169806927" type="C">Formal Methods</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-45251-6_30</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.45264">Discrete mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.54398">Heuristic</keyword><keyword weight="0.44212">State vector</keyword><keyword weight="0.51793">Model checking</keyword><keyword weight="0.55218">Graph isomorphism</keyword><keyword weight="0.43828">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.45669">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.51243">Isomorphism</keyword><keyword weight="0.51198">Equivalence class</keyword><keyword weight="0.50819">SPIN model checker</keyword><keyword weight="0.44791">Choice function</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>We present four versions of a new heuristic for coping with the problem of finding (canonical) representatives of symmetry equivalence classes (the so-called orbit problem), in symmetry techniques for model checking. The practical implementation of such techniques hinges on appropriate workarounds of this hard problem, which is equivalent to graph isomorphism. We implemented the four strategies on top of the Spin model checker, and compared their performance on several examples, with encouraging results.</abstract></paper>